Force glFinish() instead of glFlush() in the implicit-sync fallback path.

NVIDIA's proprietary/open driver does not honor wlroots' implicit-sync
assumption: when a Wayland client (e.g. WebKitGTK) does not opt into the
explicit-sync protocol, wlroots reaches the glFlush() branch in pass.c,
hands the buffer to KMS immediately, and NVIDIA may scan out before the
GPU has finished writing the frame -- producing a periodic full-frame
black flash whose rate scales with rendering workload.

glFinish() blocks until GPU work completes, restoring the invariant
wlroots assumes. Same fix the AUR `wlroots-nvidia` package uses; updated
for the 0.19 file layout (gles2_bind_buffer was refactored into pass.c).

--- a/render/gles2/pass.c
+++ b/render/gles2/pass.c
@@ -57,7 +57,7 @@
 			goto out;
 		}
 	} else {
-		glFlush();
+		glFinish();
 	}

 	ok = true;
